  },
  {
    question: "How are glitter tattoos removed?",
    answer:
      "Glitter tattoos fade and shed gradually on their own. To remove one sooner, gentle soap and warm water or a little baby oil on a cloth can help lift the design when appropriate. Avoid harsh scrubbing, which can irritate the skin.",
  },
  {
    question: "What ages are glitter tattoos best for?",
    answer:
      "Glitter tattoos work well across a wide range of ages and are especially popular with older kids and teens who can sit still for a couple of minutes. For younger children, designs are placed where they are less likely to be rubbed, and any design can be skipped if a child prefers.",
  },
  {
    question: "Can glitter tattoos be added to face painting?",
    answer:
      "Yes. Glitter tattoos pair well with face painting as part of a two-service party mix, and they also pair with balloon twisting and face gems. Combining services keeps each station moving and gives guests more variety. Final pricing is reviewed after you submit your event details.",
